 length of Krome Avenue included: widening the road from two to four lanes, reconstructing roadways and shoulders, Constructing new non-motorized, multi-use trails, realigning intersections, installing a 40-foot median in some parts, new guardrails, drainage systems, lighting, signage, and pavement markings. if(typeof __ez_fad_position != 'undefined'){__ez_fad_position('div-gpt-ad-constructionreviewonline_com-medrectangle-4-0')};The projects “address safety, flooding, water quality, economic competitiveness and preservation of the existing roadway,” FDOT Project Manager Jonathan Fundora said, adding that FDOT programs with similar projects to improve Krome Avenue have been in the works since 1999. “Widening the roadway was critical in providing a safer, more efficient commute for drivers in the area, and the multi-use path provides a dedicated trail for bicyclists and pedestrians,” he added.